subject: Re: How do I submit code which I think should be added to  JUnit?
msgSnippet: ... members of the community to post request for changes, ... (five stars is five votes). ... Mike, Does http://sourceforge.net/projects/junit/ do what you
messageBody:
--- In junit@y..., "Mike Duffy" <mike.duffy@c...> wrote:

> Perhaps there could be a section on the junit.org site that allows
members of the community to post request for changes,
> make comments on the existing posts and keeps a weighted counter
(five stars is five votes).
>
> Mike

Mike,

Does http://sourceforge.net/projects/junit/ do what you need? It's got
a bug list, forums and all the usual SourceForge stuff.

Dave
